article.description: North Carolina A&T cruises by Greensboro 91-64
article.headline: North Carolina A&T cruises by Greensboro 91-64
article.linkText: North Carolina A&T cruises by Greensboro 91-64
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- Richaud Pack scored 30 points to lead North Carolina A&T over Division III Greensboro 91-64 on Friday night. In his first game as an Aggie, Pack missed only three shots. He finished 7 for 9 from the field and 13 of 14 on free throws. Lamont Middleton added 27 points on 8-of-13 shooting. North Carolina A&T shot 19 of 23 from the field and six of seven 3-pointers in the second half as they ran away from Greensboro. Tracy Jester scored 18 points and Damian Dixon added 14 for Greensboro who challenged the Aggies early. The Aggies trailed by as much as seven before they tied the game at 22 with 7:34 left in the first half and went on an 18-9 run to end the first half. North Carolina A&T now leads the series 2-0 between the schools which are only two miles apart.
